    <svcproc id="s26510.2.1" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Boost Control Solenoid (BCS)</title>
        <figure id="s26510.2.2.1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign09/N09006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>BCS assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The BSC assembly is a two position valve that controls intake manifold boost pressure to the turbocharger
            pneumatic actuator.
        </para>
        <para>The ECM sends signals to the BCS assembly to control the turbocharger pneumatic actuator which controls
            the turbocharger bypass valve and turbocharger boost.
        </para>
        <para>The BCS is mounted on the air inlet elbow.</para>
    </svcproc>
